Yobe state Governor-elect, Hon Mai Mala Buni, and his deputy, Idi Barda Gubana have been sworn to replace Governor Ibrahim Gaidam as his tenure expired some minutes ago. The oath of office and oath of allegiance was administered to them by the Chief Judge of Yobe state, Justice Musa Nabaruma, at the Banquet Hall of Government House, Damaturu. The ceremony was conducted amidst resounding cheers and thunderous ovation from the mammoth crowd, just as residents have high expectations from the incoming administration. Remarking on his achievements, the outgoing governor, Ibrahim Gaidam, recounted how the demise of his late boss, Senator Mamman Ali of blessed memory ushered him into power in January 2009.  Details later â€¦ Yobe commissioner quits to became Deputy Governor Yobe commissioner quits to vie for dep gov INEC releases particulars of 2 guber candidates in Yobe Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin